[NAME]
Chickpea Hummus
[INGREDIENTS]
2/3 Cup : Chickpeas (garbanzo beans, bengal gram), mature seeds, canned, drained, rinsed in tap water
3 Cups : Beverages, water, tap, drinking
2 Cloves : Garlic, raw
1 : Spices, bay leaf
3/4 Tsp : Salt, table
1 Tbsp : Oil, olive, salad or cooking
3/4 Cup : Onions, young green, tops only
2 Tbsp : Lemon juice, raw
3 Tbsp : Coriander (cilantro) leaves, raw
1 Tsp : Spices, cumin seed
[DIRECTIONS]
In a large saucepan over high heat, combine the chickpeas, water, garlic cloves, bay leaf and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat to low, cover partially, and simmer until the beans are very tender, 50-60 minutes.
Drain and discard the bay leaf, reserving the garlic and 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid.
In a blender or food processor, combine the chickpeas, cooked garlic, olive oil, the 3/4 cup green onion, lemon juice, cilantro, cumin, and the remaining 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Process to puree. 
Add the reserved cooking liquid, 1 tablespoon at a time, until the mixture has the consistency of a thick spread.
In a small bowl, stir together the chickpea mixture and the remaining 2 tablespoons green onion.
Serve immediately, or cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
[PREPTIME]
1 hour
[SERVINGS]
6
